<h2>Group skiing FAQs </h2>
<p><strong>Do you offer discounts when booking as a group?</strong> - Yes, we offer 5% discount for groups of 10 or more. </p>
<p><strong>How do I book a group holiday?</strong> - For group numbers over 9, please contact our <a data-udi="umb://document/e5b8abf94a554299a3960566b88e9193" href="/{localLink:umb://document/e5b8abf94a554299a3960566b88e9193}" title="Contact Us">Reservations Team</a> directly. </p>
<p><strong>Can private group transfers be arranged?</strong> - <span>We can offer private transfers for guests booking a full package with flights and accommodation. You can book a private transfer up to 14 days before departure. Please see <a data-udi="umb://document/9b67579eaa2748aeae6357891f20ff01" href="/{localLink:umb://document/9b67579eaa2748aeae6357891f20ff01}" title="Transfers">here</a> for more details. </span></p>
<p><span><strong>Is a chalet, hotel or apartment better for a group ski holiday?</strong> - This will mainly be down to personal preference and what kind of time you are planning to spend together as a group. Chalets are great for spending your down time together, relaxing in the lounge area. Apartments are ideal if you all want to get together and join in with cooking up delicious meals. Hotels are perfect if you want to retire to your own rooms be sure to dine together at a pre-booked restaurant on-site or locally. </span></p>
<p><span><strong>Which resorts have the best après ski for groups?</strong> - Europe is certainly known for it's après ski so there won't be many resorts that don't offer this. However some top places for après ski we would recommend if you are travelling in a group are <a data-udi="umb://document/a95de5322c984f85bcf0f013c457e8df" href="/{localLink:umb://document/a95de5322c984f85bcf0f013c457e8df}" title="Davos">Davos</a> in Switzerland and <a data-udi="umb://document/acff50eb9ad84862a464f68b551bc497" href="/{localLink:umb://document/acff50eb9ad84862a464f68b551bc497}" title="Alpe d'Huez">Alpe d'Huez</a> in France. These resorts offer fun après ski, but with a wide choice of relaxed pubs, elegant bars and loud clubs so there is something for everyone. Due to these resorts also being fairly large, they work well for groups. </span></p>
<p><strong>What if we aren't all skiers, but want to go on a group holiday?</strong> - This is certainly no problem at our resorts. There are so many alternatives. Out on the snow you can cross-ski, toboggan or play a game of curling. Away from the snow, many of our hotels and chalets offer spas with treatments, pools, saunas and more. There are always plenty of bars, restaurants and shops to explore also. For our Finland/Lapland holiday you can also enjoy husky rides, feeding reindeer and searching for the Northern Lights. </p>
<p><strong>Can we rent ski clothes and equipment?</strong> - All resorts offer ski rental stores and once we have helped you book your destination, we can help advise where and what to rent. </p>
<p><strong>Are there any terms and conditions to group discounts?</strong> - Yes, please see T&amp;Cs below.</p>
</div>
</div>
<h2 style="text-align: left;">Travel with confidence </h2>
<p>When you choose an Inghams holiday, you can travel with confidence. We’re here to take the stress out of travelling. We’ve put extra measures in place for your peace of mind. We’ll help keep both you and your money safe.</p>
